{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, Raina et al. (2003) introduce a hybrid 1 3 model that integrates both generative and discriminative classifiers.",
    "The hybrid model is designed to leverage the strengths of both approaches: generative classifiers' effectiveness in conditions of limited training data and discriminative classifiers' accuracy with abundant labeled data.",
    "Their hybrid approach leads to lower test errors and better performance than purely generative or discriminative models, especially in scenarios with varying training data sizes.",
    "Leveraging these concepts, we can propose an integration of the hybrid generative and discriminative model approach to enhance fossil analysis.",
    "Specifically, the hybrid model's generative aspect can manage sparse and often incomplete fossil records, while its discriminative part ensures precision with larger datasets."
  ]
}